baseName.value: Self-locking pavers for external flooring to the BIG series

generalComment.value: The specific site data of the production phase refer to 2020 and were supplied by Micheletto s.a.s.. The upstream and downstream processes were modeled on the basis of data from the Ecoinvent database 3.7.1. The contribution of generic data on deliverables is less than 4% for each category of impact. Packaging of raw materials and packaging, consumption of methane for heating, infrastructure and business travel, consumption of diesel for the scraper used for internal handling and oil lubricant are excluded.

BIG
Thickness: 120 mm (± 2 mm) – Weight: 270 kg/sqm – Size: 250x500; 500x500; 500x750; 500x1000; 1000x1000 (mm) – Maximum diagonal difference: 2K Class (3 mm) – Maximum convexity: 1,5 mm – Maximum cavity: 1,0 mm – Asbestos emissions: None – Reaction to fire: A1 Class – Water absorption durability: =6% – Characteristic bending strength: =3,5 Mpa – Breaking load per unit length: Satisfactory – Quartz double layer abrasion resistance: 4I Class (imprint =20 mm) – Slip/skid: =60 – Thermal conductivity: Not applicable – Behaviour to external fire: Satisfactory

technologicalApplicability.value:
Micheletto produces a wide range of products which, thanks to technical and functional characteristics in addition to their ability to resist great stresses and intense passage flows of both static and moving heavy vehicles, can be used in industrial plants, large sports and residential complexes, shopping malls, airports and public buildings. The products under study are self-locking pavers used for outdoor flooring and belonging to the BIG, ELITE, PREMIUM and RI-MADE series. The paving generally consists of two layers: the base layer (which provides the mechanical resistance) and the surface layer (made with high quality natural stones, coloring oxides and additives).
 BIG: The self-locking paver BIG is intended for professionals who design flooring with large slabs and with high thicknesses, both for public and private works. The product is ideal for applications with very high loads and frequent passage of vehicles.
